column10:
Far Cry 4 is an open world first person shooter set in the fictional country of Kyrat in the beautiful Himalayan Mountains. Overall it is a fun and engrossing game. However, in my opinion it is far too similar to Far Cry 3 in terms of gameplay, arsenal, progression and narrative structure. I can recommend it if you don't mind repetition and are not tired of the 'Ubisoft formula'.

Pros:
- Good optimisation;
- Interesting setting;
- Colorful visuals;
- Great sound design and soundtrack;
- Good arsenal;
- Fun stealth;
- Interesting story;
- Great gunplay;
- Good AI;
- Responsive controls;
- Fun traversal;
- Great environmental storytelling;
- Good voice acting;

Cons:
- Ubisoft Connect(Upaly) is complete trash;
- Too easy;
- Boring radio;
- Most side missions are boring;
- Too similar to Far Cry 3;
- Gameplay loop can get very repetitive;

void loop()
{
  yes (yes(yes));

